review_blob: Bottle, 33cl. Light yellow, foggy. Typical saison aroma, with some citrus from the Citra hops. Too carbonated, but fresh taste!-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

Bottle, 375ml. Wake up and smell the coffee! Black and medium thick. Little head. Well balanced taste of roast, coffee and vanilla. And that rye! A little too bubbly in the mouth for this type of beer, but all in all very good!-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

Bottle, 25 cl. Thick, black and creamy. Ring of brown foam that hangs on the glass. Smells of raisins, nuts, chocolate and malt. Taste of roasted coffee. Slightly too foamy when drinking. Alcohol taste is balanced.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Bottle, 50cl. Deep red, cloudy. Little head. Nutty smell of malt and hops. Rather bitter, with long-hanging bitter aftertaste.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

Bottle, 375ml. Smells a bit like red wine, but mostly raisins, thus reminding of glhwein. Dark brown/red, doesnt look that inviting. Raisin taste is strong, gives me a Christmas feeling.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Bottle, 33cl. Nice sour with aroma of wild berries. Taste is well balanced with aroma.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

Bottle, 50cl. Complex aroma with coriander, citrus and hops. Gives me an appetite for a proper ramen soup. Taste is coherent with aroma. Alcohol does not stand out, just gives a richer taste.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
beer_name: gir / Beavertown Bver Double White IPA

review_blob: Bottle, 33cl. Thick aroma of malt, dried apricot and walnut. Palate not as thick as expected. Taste and aroma go well together. Medium brown.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

Bottle, 33cl. Wonderful aroma! I cant stop smelling this. Dried fruits, plum, chocolate. Very well balanced. Taste corresponds well with aroma. Thin line of light brown, creamy foam around the edge.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Bottle, 33cl. Thick, black and creamy. Aroma with dried fruits and nuts. Roasted malt and raw coffee. Aftertaste slightly too much burned.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Bottle, 50cl. Wonderful color! Deep red, makes a promise of sour red berries. And it keeps the promise! One of the most sour beers Ive had. Lots of cherry taste here.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Bottle, 33cl. Wonderful smell of flowers, deep golden orange, cloudy - promising. But the taste is a bit weak, and bitterness is a bit over the top.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
beer_name: Mikkeller I Wish Gluten Free IPA

review_blob: Bottle, 33cl. Nice colour, deep copper. Thick, strong. Hint of citrus, plum and raisin.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Bottle, 50cl. Beautiful colour, dark golden with hint of red. Taste reminds of rye. Hoppy aroma. Faint hint of red berries.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Bottle, 33cl. Reminds of a Belgian beer, smells of yeast. Fresh, but too carbonated.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Bottle, 50 cl. This is strange. But nice. Hint of cherry, slightly burned. Fresh and heavy at the same time.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Bottle, 50 cl. Fresh smell of citrus. Reminds remotely of saison, as it has some acidity. Plain and bitter aftertaste.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Bottle, 33cl. Nice coffee aroma. Black! Thick, creamy. Strong taste of coffee, medium bitterness. Fresh.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Bottle, 33 cl. Belgian bomb of dried and fresh fruits. Smells like a sour, tastes like a tripel.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Bottle, 50 cl. Nice aroma. Deep red/brown colour. Roasted malt, mature cherry. Hint of nuts.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Bottle, 50 cl. This smoked style of beer is growing on me. A hint of berries, but not much.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Bottle, 50 cl. Crisp and spicy, nice Saison. Well balanced. Good for warm summer days.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

Bottle, 50 cl. Both aroma and taste have a strong hint of lemongrass. Refreshing, but underneath is an ordinary pale ale, so the overall taste experience is not as exciting as expected. Good for warm summer nights.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

Bottle 33cl, Vinmonopolet. Like most fruit beers, it takes a few sips to get used to this. But when accustomed to the taste, I want more. Lightly sour, the rhubarb taste is pleasant and signignificant in the aftertaste.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Tap, Katedralen. Smells nice, but is too thin, almost like lager. No aftertaste to speak of.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Tap, Crowbar. Smells chocolate! A bit thin, perhaps. Taste of chocolate, hint og coffee.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Tap, Crowbar. Crisp saison, hint of smoke? Grapefruit. Banana. Bitter aftertaste.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Bottle 50 cl, Vinmonopolet. Typical IPA aroma, lots of hops. Bitter smoke, not too much.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

Bottle 50 cl, Vinmonopolet. Nice smell and looks, and ok taste. Not too much fruit taste and sourness, which happens with some sours. The bubbles remind more of sparkling wine. Which is what I think this should probably rather be. Id like to taste this as a redcurrent sparkling wine, not so much as a beer. Nevertheless, decent sour.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Tap, Crowbar. Smells like wood and fruit. Surprisingly bitter for 65 IBU. Bitter aftertaste, pine.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Bottle 50cl, Vinmonopolet. This IPA is very well balanced, with lots of taste from hops, but not too much bitterness.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

Bottle, 50 cl, Vinmonopolet. Rye, dried fruits, smoke. Thick, pours like thin syrup. Dark brown, yet not opaque. Title is appropriate - this beer is suitable for when the sun turns.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Bitter! Smell of sea. Lots of hops, thick and creamy. Bottle 33cl, Vinmonopolet.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Typical pale ale, without any fuzz. Plain and simple malt and bitterness. Richer than a lager, but not by much.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

The aroma is intimidating, forewarning a heavy brew. But the taste is not that heavy after all. Rich, but not too much. Sweet, malt, rye (even though there isnt any), dried fruits, hops.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Not very exciting, but a decent pale ale. Hint of wood, almost no hops. Bitter aftertaste.
Very rich in taste! Chocolate, coffee and a long lasting aftertaste of burnt malt. Hangs on the sides of the glass, looks beautiful.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Nice lager. Crisp, quite bitter. Not very exciting, smell of malt. Good colour.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

Probably one of the worlds best and most well-balanced IPAs. Good smell of hops, good taste with hint of citrus, not too bitter, nice brown-orange colour, and not too clear.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Smooth drinking. A bit too burnt for my taste. Lots of taste, especially coffee. Feels thin in aftertaste, only bitter and burnt remains.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
beer_name: All In Brewing / Lervig Imperial Porter

review_blob: Bottle 50cl. Crisp, suitable for hot summer days. Citrus, hoppy aftertaste. Good alternative to plain pale ale, without going into IPA-land.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Smells like harvest. Very suitable after doing garden work. Hint of smoke, tastes like farming.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Nice IPA, but not too exciting. Little smell, strong grapefruit aftertaste.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Big smell of hops. Extremely bitter, almost over the top. Feels thick and smooth.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Takes a few sips to adjust to the taste, but it gets better and better. Wonderful smell and colour.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
